source.name: Public Health Statistics- Chlamydia cases among females aged 15-44 in Chicago, by year, 2000-2011.
source.description: The annual number of newly reported, laboratory-confirmed cases of chlamydia (Chlamydia trachomatis) among females aged 15-44 years and annual chlamydia incidence rate (cases per 100,000 females aged 15-44 years) with corresponding 95% confidence intervals by Chicago community area, for years 2000 – 2011.  See full description at https://data.cityofchicago.org/api/assets/49B861B6-11ED-4BAA-BAD1-F1B9BEFFD458.
